          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2021-01-12T14:33:47Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Protecting our Students in Schools Act of 2020</b></p> <p>This bill prohibits the use of corporal punishment in schools that receive federal funding. It also establishes enforcement provisions, including a private right of action for a student who has been subjected to corporal punishment, and creates a grant program for state educational agencies to implement positive behavioral interventions and supports to address student behavior and reduce exclusionary and aversive discipline practices. </p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2020-12-01T05:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in Senate</name>
